import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { getProducts, getOrders, getCustomers } from '../services/api'; import { Link } from 'react-router-dom'; const Dashboard = () => { const [stats, setStats] = useState({ totalRentals: 0, activeRentals: 0, totalRevenue: 0, totalProducts: 0, totalCustomers: 0 }); const [recentOrders, setRecentOrders] = useState([]); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true); useEffect(() => { loadDashboardData(); }, []); const loadDashboardData = async () => { try { const [ordersRes, productsRes, customersRes] = await Promise.all([ getOrders().catch(() => ({ data: [] })), getProducts().catch(() => ({ data: [] })), getCustomers().catch(() => ({ data: [] })) ]); const orders = ordersRes.data || []; const products = productsRes.data || []; const customers = customersRes.data || []; // Calculate stats const activeRentals = orders.filter(order => order.status === 'confirmed' || order.status === 'pending' ).length; const totalRevenue = orders.reduce((sum, order) => sum + (parseFloat(order.total_amount) || 0), 0 ); setStats({ totalRentals: orders.length, activeRentals, totalRevenue, totalProducts: products.length, totalCustomers: customers.length }); // Get recent orders (last 5) setRecentOrders(orders.slice(0, 5)); } catch (error) { console.error('Error loading dashboard data:', error); } finally { setLoading(false); } }; if (loading) { return (
